cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR

The paper discusses bibliometric techniques for measuring the impact of scientific publications, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the organization and retrieval of digital information, including scientific publications. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as it deals with the analysis and retrieval of information from large datasets, which is relevant to the analysis of citation data. cs.CY (Computational Biology) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are less likely but still possible categories as they both involve the analysis of large datasets and networks. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a possible category as it deals with the analysis of data security and privacy, which is relevant to the analysis of bibliographic data.
